I hate to be controversial, but I would prefer to simply recommend `"type": "module"` as the standard approach:

> In order to use modules with `.js` extensions, ensure you have a package.json file with `"type": "module"` set:

```js
// package.json
{
  "name": "app",
  "...",
  "type": "module"
}
```
